<dl id="n41038f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n41" href="#n41038f">N41 (VI.B.33)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n41all.htm#n41038f"> 38(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> dower 1&frasl;3</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Before 1883 a wife was entitled on her husband&apos;s death to <mark>&ldquo;Dower,&ldquo; that is to a third part</mark> of his inheritable freehold property for her life. <small> Maud I. Crofts, <a name="MICW" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#MICW"><cite title="source">Women under English Law</cite></a>, 1st ed. (1925) 36</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
